---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE } from "../consts";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <BaseHead
            title={`About &middot; ${SITE_TITLE}`}
            description="About Drypod — who's writing here, and why."
        />
    </head>
    <body>
        <Header />
        <main>
            <h1>About</h1>

            <p>
                I go by <strong>Drypod</strong> online. The real name stays off the
                internet &mdash; partly for privacy, partly because the work should
                matter more than the person.
            </p>

            <h2>The short version</h2>
            <p>
                I live in Chennai, India. By day I'm a Senior Solution
                Consultant in data &mdash; master data management, data quality,
                data governance, the unglamorous plumbing that keeps large
                organisations from drowning in their own information. Before
                that I spent three years as a Java developer, so I've seen both
                sides: writing code and selling the platform the code runs on.
            </p>

            <h2>The longer version</h2>
            <p>
                I'm a B.Tech in Instrumentation and Control Engineering (2016),
                which means I studied a little bit of everything and ended up
                specialised in something none of my professors predicted. Ten
                years in IT, one pandemic-shaped career break, and a slow pivot
                from "write the software" to "make the data trustworthy" later,
                here I am.
            </p>
            <p>
                I'm not an expert in any single thing. I'm a generalist with a
                serious curiosity problem &mdash; which is exactly why this blog
                exists. When something grabs me, I go deep on it for a few
                weeks, take notes, form opinions, argue with myself, and
                eventually write it down. By then I've usually moved on to the
                next thing. The blog is the trail.
            </p>

            <h2>What I care about</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Directness over diplomacy.</strong> I'd rather be useful
                    than nice. If something is bad, I'll say it's bad and why.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Systems over willpower.</strong> Kaizen (small continuous
                    improvement) and Shukan (habit-building) beat motivation every
                    time. Most "self-improvement" content is theatre; I'm interested
                    in what actually compounds.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Honest accounts over victory laps.</strong> I log the
                    failures, the streaks I broke, the plans that collapsed in week
                    two. If this blog only showed the wins, it would be useless.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Power and incentives, not vibes.</strong> Whether it's
                    office politics, geopolitics, or a video game economy, I want
                    to know who benefits and how. Machiavelli over motivational posters.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>What I do when I'm not writing here</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Tinker with AI tools, self-hosted software, and 3D printing
                    on my Bambu A1 Mini.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Play strategy and city-builder games &mdash; the kind where
                    you manage an economy, not the kind where you save the
                    world.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Read webnovels and novels &mdash; Chinese web fiction, the
                    occasional fantasy/sci-fi novel, whatever pulls me in.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Write fiction. One long-running project is a
                    Chinese-web-novel-style contemporary fantasy set in Tokyo.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Lift badly, walk a lot, and try to undo 10+ hours a day of
                    sitting.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Track my money obsessively and still make questionable
                    decisions.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Why "Drypod"</h2>
            <p>
                Because the domain was available and I liked the sound of it.
                That's the whole story.
            </p>

            <h2>Contact</h2>
            <p>
                The blog doesn't have comments wired up yet &mdash; when real
                traffic justifies it, I'll add them. Until then, find me through
                the social links in the footer, or just sit with the post for a
                bit. Most things don't need a reply.
            </p>
        </main>
        <Footer />
    </body>
</html>

<style>
    main {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2em 1em 4em;
        color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
        line-height: 1.6;
    }
    h1 {
        margin-bottom: 0.5em;
    }
    h2 {
        margin-top: 1.5em;
        margin-bottom: 0.5em;
    }
    p {
        margin-bottom: 1em;
    }
    ul {
        padding-left: 1.25em;
        margin-bottom: 1em;
    }
    li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5em;
    }
    a {
        color: var(--accent);
        text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
    }
</style>
